<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1478,1755]" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1586,1611]" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other genera in 
<taxonomicName box="[751,846,1586,1611]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[751,846,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade by plumage. Gray males differ from all but 
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,1622,1647]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Myrmoborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which distinguished by black throats and dark crowns. Females distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1291,1436,1622,1647]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1291,1436,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Myrmoborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by dark or contrasting crown and either lack of dark face mask or white in underparts. Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1365,1658,1683]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Pyriglena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1365,1658,1683]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Pyriglena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in tail length and bill length proportions. Domed-shaped nest differs from nest of 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1141,1695,1718]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1141,1695,1718]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Myrmeciza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sandy soil forest habitat preference supportive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
